Internet marketing helped me set up my mindset as an online entrepreneur. I didn&rsquo;t have that mindset when I started last year. I wanted to taste financial freedom, I was alured by passive income things and when I began my journey shiny object syndrome started to kick in&hellip;
There are overwhelming amount of shiny objects in this niche. So, how did Internet Marketing helped me set up my mindset as an entrepreneur?
To be honest, there are only a handful of resources that helped me understand the fundamentals of the business. Mindset plays an important role for sure. First, this FREE program helped me understand my shiny object syndrome and gave me the peace of mind that was needed to make this business a success&hellip;
Then someone shared me a recording of Dan Lok&rsquo;s workshop which helped me understand about the myth people are holding around passive income and financial freedom&hellip;In this blog I am going to dive into that&hellip;
(These are the myths Dan says blocking you from earning massive passive income)
Myth # 1 - Financial Freedom Most people dream to be financially free so that they don&rsquo;t have to do any work when they retire&hellip; this is the myth no. 1 though&hellip;!
Financial freedom is an illusion, it doesn&rsquo;t exist.
Look at those billionaires we see everyday appearing in news like Mark Zuckerberg, Jeff Bezos, Elon Musk, Bill Gates, they have no shortage of money in their bank to live a financially free life but they haven&rsquo;t chosen to live that life by sitting on beach, doing nothing&hellip;because financial freedom is a thing sold by gurus which is an outdated things&hellip;
This is what Dan Lok said about the myth:
Most people don&rsquo;t want to retire, but they want to do what retired people want to do&hellip;
And creative people can&rsquo;t stay without creating things and adding value to the marketplace&hellip;
There is a mindset shift we all need to have&hellip;
Don&rsquo;t aim for financial freedom, aim for financial confidence
Myth # 2 - Passive Income Passive income is not a myth in the sense that it does exist unlike financial freedom&hellip; but it is a myth in the sense how people perceive this to be &ndash; like something passive aka effortless, easy and quick&hellip;
The TRUTH is generating passive income is not easy, and it takes a lot of hard work and long time to build&hellip;
ANOTHER truth is even if you become successful to generate some form of passive income through your hard work, don&rsquo;t think that it would stay like this forever&hellip;
This is what Dan Lok wants us to remember:
Just because it is passive, doesn&rsquo;t mean it is permanent
So even passive income is true this is not something we should think of&hellip; Dan challenges that you won&rsquo;t find the word &ldquo;passive income&rdquo; in the vocabulary of the billionaires I mentioned above&hellip;just watch some of their interviews online and try to find that word&hellip;
So in a nutshell passive income is also a myth as in reality nothing is passive.. nobody follows a passive leader&hellip; you can&rsquo;t achieve a good health in passive ways&hellip; anything worthwile can&rsquo;t be done passively&hellip;you have to work at it..
Dan poses an interesting question to all of us&hellip;
If passive health doesn&rsquo;t work, passive sex doesn&rsquo;t work&hellip;how would passive income work?
So the lesson Dan Lok wants us to remember:
Don&rsquo;t aim for passive income aim for leveraged income
The workshope is full of golden nuggets, I shared just two of them&hellip;.
I highly recommend each one of you to watch the whole recording&hellip; it&rsquo;s going to blow your mind with values and shift your mindset&hellip;
Heres the link to watch the workshop: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jmNdho2svuc

When someone starts online marketing, traffic may be the first thing they struggle to understand for the first time&hellip; Soon they realize it is not the vehicles we used to see on roads&hellip;it is we people who are targeted to the offer or solution&hellip;
After traffic, lead generation comes into play&hellip;
The difference I see is not clearly understood by many&hellip;
Traffic vs Lead So what is the difference between traffic and lead?
Traffic and lead both refers to people in online marketing&hellip;
But they are not the same, have a slight but crucial difference..
Traffic is your target audience&hellip;
For example, if you have a diet pill for obese people, then all the obese people online are are your target people aka traffic
Now leads are also traffic but not all the traffic are leads&hellip;
Leads are only interested people to your offers&hellip;
For example, you put your ads on somewhere your traffic hangs out which says you have got a pill that can help obese man and women lose 10 pounds in 30 days&hellip;
And you put the ads in a Weight Loss Facebook group&hellip;
That means all the people there are your target audience aka traffic as they joined the group with an intention to lose weight&hellip; If the group has 2000 members, all the 2000 people are your traffic&hellip;
But you got only 10 people interested in your offer&hellip;
So out of all the 2000 people you generated 10 leads who are interested in your offer&hellip;
I have written on this topic as I have been asked by many people that how to generate traffic&hellip;
The question is wrong in my opinion&hellip;
Traffic can&rsquo;t be generated, it is already there, you just need to found them&hellip;
Leads can be generated with proper ads and following proven strategies&hellip;
That&rsquo;s my take from these two terms&hellip;.
Selling vs Closing Let&rsquo;s talk about Sell vs Close&hellip;
Primarily I also thought that both terms have the same meaning and can be used interchangeably&hellip;and I have seen many people use it interchangeably&hellip;.
But then I found that they are not the same&hellip; Again has a subtle but important distinction in between&hellip;
To understand the difference I would like to recall a quote from The wolf of wall street documentary&hellip; where you will hear the following Ben Affleck&rsquo;s quote (which is worth remembering btw):
A sale is made on every call you make. Either you sell the client some stock or he sells you a reason he can&rsquo;t. Either way a sale is made, the only question is: Who is gonna close?
This quote should be understood in the context of cold calling&hellip;
If you understand the quote you know a sale can be made without paying anything, you can sell a concept, an idea, a promise, a perspective, a logic or a reason as well&hellip;and most important aspect here is that &ndash; selling is a process.
If selling is a process, then closing is the final destination of the process&hellip;if you can sell an idea, a promise etc, you can then close it by offering something irresistible to the lead&hellip;.this is how you close the sell&hellip;
But if you try to sell a big promise but the lead raises a bigger objection not to go for it&hellip;.you failed to handle the objection in selling process and you failed to close and the deal is closed by the lead instead without any monetary transaction&hellip;
Why understanding the differences is crucial? It is important to understand the differences otherwise you will struggle to prioritize your focus&hellip;
If you are just beginning focus on how to find traffic&hellip;
When you got a good traffic source just focus on lead generation&hellip;
If you become skilled at generating leads then focus more on how to sell your offer to them&hellip;
And if you find that your sales process taking too much time and effort and yielding less profits then surely there&rsquo;s something wrong in your closing part&hellip;it is time to become skilled at closing&hellip;.
So I think the above post was helpful to understand the differences between Traffic vs Leads, Sale vs Close &hellip;.
Want more clarity like this? I have a clarity doc on affiliate marketing, where I demystified it for complete newbies&hellip; you can get clarity and save money by getting the knowledge from the doc and also you will receive updates on my latest blog posts through email&hellip; find the clarity doc in the top menu bar.

Yesterday I saw an advertisement on Facebook, which caught my attention. I remember I saw it several times, even read comments before. But today while I was reading the comments, I saw one comment clearly stood out from the rest. Although it wasn&rsquo;t an affiliate&rsquo;s comment, I took a few important lessons for my audience. Internalized properly and it can help you make affiliate marketing work, everytime&hellip;
The Facebook Ads Above I mentioned the Facebook ads on 7-figure email system. It is a $4.79 product, so a very cheap product in deed. Below the ads there were a lot of comments from intersted people asking different questions. But one of those comments got 60+ likes and this is where I want you to focus now&hellip;
The Copywriter&rsquo;s Comment So, the exact comment that I want you to look for is from a copywriter named Nico Sanchez. He is a copywriter who has a brand named &ldquo;Copy Nomad&rdquo;&hellip; and I guess he has a good reputation and following&hellip;
He purchased the $4.79 product and shared his experience in the comment:
&ldquo;initially bought this cause it it&rsquo;s clearly an AC funnel&hellip; gotta say as a copywriter with 10+ years experience I&rsquo;m pleasantly surprised by the quality. Lots of stuff I use, but also great new stuff I want to implement.&rdquo; - Nico Sanchez
Nothing fancy, he just shared his experience after purchasing the product. But see three other comments after his comment&hellip; they purchased the product without overthinking&hellip; one guy asked for his further opinion&hellip;
Now just consider the same case in the context of affiliate marketing. What if the company who advertised allows affiliate to promote their product for a commission? What if you become an affiliate of them&hellip; how should you help people make a purchase decision?
What Went Right? I want you always remember this ads and the copywriter&rsquo;s comment to answer the question. Because it surely worked, naturally. So there must be something gone right, let me break it down:
He is a professional copywriter which means he has some level of expertise on this He purchased the product first of all He has gone through the product He shared his initial expectation and real experience in natural language The 2 people who readily bought the product must be a follower of the copywriter, so they have the trust on him&hellip; The 3rd person who asked for further opinion, might not be following him, but he got persuaded by either the comment of the copywriter (he mentioned that he has 10+ years experience) or the other two people who purchased it based on the copywriter&rsquo;s recommendation. The copywriter shared his surprise on the quality of the product. My Takeaways So what&rsquo;s your take aways if you want to make affiliate marketing work for you?
Here&rsquo;s mine:
Gain expertise on what you are promoting, so that you can become a trusted advisor on that subject&hellip; Purchase what you want to promote Share your real experience with people in your own language Build a following by sharing your journey and providing value Tell people about you and also let your followers tell about you Always promote quality products because people love to buy quality products Hopefully the above example and takeaways were clear to you&hellip; if you need more clarity on how affiliate marketing works, then I have a clarity doc on the top menu bar of this site. I am sure you will find the clarity doc more insightful&hellip;

In my previous post I discussed about my smartphone-friendly side hustle. And you know by now that it is called Affilaite Marketing.
In affiliate marketing you don&rsquo;t need to have your own product&hellip;
You promote other peoples product&hellip; and for each sale you get commission&hellip;
Although it is as simple as that I see most people still wonders &ldquo;how can I start?&rdquo;
I will answer this topic in this post&hellip;
To start affiliate marketing you have to know the answer of the following three questions, and I am giving you the questions and possible answer here in my post&hellip;
Q1. What affiliate products to choose? Answer: There are a lot of products to choose from and it won&rsquo;t cost you a penny to become an affiliate of most products. Still I see a lot of newbies ask in different forums &ldquo;how to get affiliate link to promote a product? On top of that there are affiliate marketplace like Clickbank, JVzoo, WarriorPlus, Digistore24 where you can find affiliate products to promote. The product you choose should be a good product that people will buy. Remember that every product has customers, but not every product sales equal. Find best selling products from those affiliate marketplaces or simply by searching on google with the following terms:
Top 10 affiliate products to promote in (your interst area)
I think you can find a lot of products to promote if you just remember these two&hellip;
Q2. Where and how to promote the product? Now I guess everyone has got a product&rsquo;s affiliate link to promote. If you have got one, the second questions will be like, where and how to find people to promote my product, in other words, how to get traffic? This is a big question in itself. I would only touch two things here. A product can be promoted through paid advertising or free organic strategies. In affiliate marketing terms, it is called Traffic/Lead Generation. One thing you need to remember is that traffic is already there, you just need to find it. By saying this I mean people are using Facebook, Tiktok, Youtube, Email so they are the traffic already passing time online. But you don&rsquo;t know how to reach them. This is where you have to put most of your focus once you have something to sale.
Q3. How to make sale? Nowadays, with the prevalence of social media, it has become easier to find traffic than before. You can find targetted traffic in different interest groups, or through your contents with the help of algorithm and without spending anything on paid ads. But still you will struggle to make sale. Because, selling is an art. You need to master the art of selling. In affiliate marketing terms it is also called conversion or closing. Simply put the closing or convesion or sales process starts when you first introduce your paid products in front of the audience. The best affiliate marketers know the art of introducing their paid offers in front of their audience without appearing salesy. And it should be something you will need learn in your journey&hellip;
That&rsquo;s it for today. If you think you have got some clarity by reading this post, then I am happy to share that I have a clarity doc which is designed to give you more clarity and save your money. If you are interested to read it, you can just go on top of the site and find the clarity doc from the menu bar.

MMO aka Money Money Online is an affiliate marketing niche you may have already heard before. So, it might seem obvious when someone starts promoting make money online products or programs he/she would start making money soon. The reality is quite different though&hellip;
On average, 95% people who starts affiliate marketing can&rsquo;t make money! Among the 5%, only 2% can make money consistently&hellip;
Now this stat might discourage you or encourage you to step into affiliate marketing&hellip;
It can discourage you for the fact that only a few percentage can make real money&hellip;
It can encourage you as well if you just think that the market is not as saturated as it looks&hellip;
It is redundant to say I see the glass half-full, not half-empty. Otherwise I couldn&rsquo;t stick with it over last 1+ year, right?
And over the years I studied why most people can&rsquo;t make money with affiliate marketing&hellip;
And without further ado I am going to reveal my findings here&hellip;
Most people can&rsquo;t make money because they take MMO word for word. All they want to do is Make Money Online, period. ~ Shafat M.
That&rsquo;s the reason they fail&hellip;
If you have seen people spamming links in groups&hellip;
If you have found strangers inviting you to business opportunity&hellip;
If you have watched those videos of people dancing and pointing fingers on how much they made money&hellip;
If you have seen those pitch, pitch, and pitch; offers, offers, and offers everyday &ndash; in social media, in youtube comments, in your email&hellip;everywhere&hellip;
Then you have probably seen it all&hellip;
Why they do so?
Because they want to make money online&hellip;
What&rsquo;s the reality?
They make 0000
Then what should you do?
You have to keep in mind the following elaboration of MMO, always:
Mindset Method Opportunity If you really want to make money online, you have to start with Mindset&hellip;
Then master a method to attract traffic and convert them into sales.
Then find the best opportunity to promote to your audience.
The sequence is important&hellip; most people starts with Opportunity&hellip; then learn some methods to promote the opportunity&hellip; and starts pitching&hellip;.skipping the mindset part alltogether&hellip;
But I want you take it sequencially, work on your mindset first and ask yourself which one you prefer &ndash; make your first sale or help that person first.
Then learn traffic and convesion&hellip; for best result learn it without having anything to sale&hellip; why? Because only then you can learn pure sales and marketing techniques&hellip; if you already have something to sale, you can&rsquo;t resist yourself to promote it, I can bet&hellip;.
Then find the best opportunity you can promote&hellip; Best opportunities are those you can stand behind and promote to your friends and family&hellip;
